casebody.data:
JJ'S BAR AND GRILL, INC., d/b/a JJ's Restaurant, et al., Appellants,
v.
USIC LOCATING SERVICES, LLC, Respondent. WD 81381 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: August 28, 2018 Thomas H. Davis, Steven G. Emerson, and Courtney J. Harrison, Kansas City, MO, Attorneys for Appellants. David B. Helms and Benjamin D. Mooneyham, St. Louis, MO, and Traci L. Martinez, Columbus, OH, Attorneys for Respondent. Before Division Two: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Presiding Judge, and Lisa White Hardwick and Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

JJ's Bar and Grill, Inc., d/b/a JJ's Restaurant and JJ's Building, LLC, appeals from the judgment entered against it by the Circuit Court of Jackson County, Missouri, awarding USIC Locating Services, LLC court costs. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
